Business Brief -- Ranger Oil Ltd.:
   Company Expects to Record
   A Charge of $10.5 Million
Ranger said last year that stock options held by the
estate would lead to a fourthquarter charge of $2.4 million
to $9.6 million, depending on how the estate disposed of
them.
   The Calgary-based oil and gas producer earned $42.4
million, or 46 cents a share, in 1990. In trading yesterday
on the New York Stock Exchange, Ranger Oil closed at $7, down
12.5 cents.